OL,3,CClub legends promise to stay in touch
OL,4,Cafter mass gathering of ex-players
OL,6,FA very popular attendee was 77-year-
OL,7,Fold former defender Dave Watson, who
OL,8,Fnow lives with dementia and was
OL,9,Faccompanied by his wife, Penny.
OL,11,FPenny said of the ex-players' party:
OL,12,F"It helps him remember things. In any
OL,13,Fkind of field, getting back together
OL,14,Fwith your peers, talking and
OL,15,Freminiscing is very important.
OL,17,F"Not just people who've got memory
OL,18,Fissues but for anyone who's actually
OL,19,Fretired, they need to get together and
OL,20,Fstimulate the brain."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
